<h1>Rails Table Preferences Demo</h1>

<p>
  This demo screen uses in-memory rows for table display and the normal
  <code>table_preferences</code> table for preference persistence.
</p>

<p>
  The generated demo also seeds one shared preset named <strong>共有ビュー</strong>.
  Select it to confirm that a normal user can load a shared preset, cannot
  delete it directly, and saves changes back into an owner preset instead of
  overwriting the shared preset.
</p>

<p>
  The demo also seeds one role preset named <strong>担当ビュー</strong> for the
  role key <code>operations</code>. If the host app configures
  <code>scope_context_method</code> to return <code>{ roles: ["operations"] }</code>,
  the selector also shows <strong>担当ビュー [role:operations]</strong> and resolves
  it before the shared preset while no owner default exists.
</p>

<p>
  The demo also seeds one organization preset named <strong>東京組織ビュー</strong>
  for the organization key <code>tokyo-hq</code>. If the host app returns
  <code>{ organization: "tokyo-hq" }</code>, the selector shows
  <strong>東京組織ビュー [organization:tokyo-hq]</strong>. With no owner default and
  no matching role default, reloading the demo resolves it before the shared preset.
</p>

<section>
  <h2>Current scope context</h2>

  <p>
    <strong>Current context:</strong>
    <% if @demo_scope_context_summary["owner_only"] %>
      owner-only
    <% else %>
      <% summary_parts = [] %>
      <% if @demo_scope_context_summary.fetch("roles", []).any? %>
        <% summary_parts << "roles: [#{@demo_scope_context_summary.fetch("roles").join(", ")}]" %>
      <% end %>
      <% if @demo_scope_context_summary["organization"].present? %>
        <% summary_parts << "organization: #{@demo_scope_context_summary["organization"]}" %>
      <% end %>
      <code><%= summary_parts.join(" / ") %></code>
    <% end %>
  </p>

  <p>
    Use this summary to confirm which scope the preset selector and default
    resolution below should reflect before comparing owner, role, and
    organization behavior.
  </p>
</section>

<p>
  Sample rows intentionally mix statuses, delivery dates, repeated customer
  prefixes, long shipping codes, long delivery notes, and memo lengths.
  Search for <strong>東京</strong> or sort by <strong>納品日</strong> /
  <strong>金額</strong> to make the differences easier to spot.
</p>

<p>
  Double-click the resize handle on <strong>配送メモ</strong> or <strong>配送コード</strong>
  to confirm auto-fit, then compare <strong>配送メモ</strong> (wrap),
  <strong>配送コード</strong> (nowrap), and <strong>備考</strong> (ellipsis)
  to see the overflow modes side by side.
</p>

<p>
  The table below also keeps <strong>受注番号</strong> pinned inside a dedicated
  horizontal scroll wrapper and shows one grouped header row
  (<strong>受注情報</strong> / <strong>得意先情報</strong> / <strong>配送情報</strong>) that follows the
  current saved visible-column order after reload, so fixed-column and column-group
  behavior can be checked without additional host-app markup first.
</p>

<style>
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-scroll {
    max-width: 100%;
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table {
    min-width: 1280px;
    border-collapse: separate;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table th,
  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table td {
    background: white;
  }

  .rails-table-preferences-demo-table__group-row th {
    background: #f3f4f6;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    text-align: left;
  }
</style>

<section>
  <h2>Export payload preview</h2>

  <p>
    This preview shows the ordered headers and column keys that the current
    saved table settings would pass into the export helper.
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Headers:</strong>
    <%= @export_payload_preview.fetch("headers", []).join(" / ") %>
  </p>

  <p>
    <strong>Column keys:</strong>
    <code><%= @export_payload_preview.fetch("column_keys", []).join(", ") %></code>
  </p>

  <p>
    Hidden columns stay out of this preview by default. Change visibility or
    order in the editor, save once, and reload to confirm that the export
    payload follows the saved table settings.
  </p>
</section>

<%= table_preferences_editor(
  table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
  settings: @table_preference_settings,
  columns: @table_columns,
  title: "デモ受注一覧の表示設定"
) %>

<%= form_with url: request.path, method: :get do %>
  <%= text_field_tag :search_word, params[:search_word], placeholder: "得意先名" %>

  <%= table_preferences_hidden_fields(
    settings: @table_preference_settings,
    columns: @table_columns
  ) %>

  <%= submit_tag "検索" %>
<% end %>

<div class="rails-table-preferences-demo-scroll">
  <%= table_preferences_table_tag(
    table_key: :rails_table_preferences_demo_orders,
    settings: @table_preference_settings,
    columns: @table_columns,
    class: "table rails-table-preferences-demo-table"
  ) do %>
    <thead>
      <% if @demo_visible_column_groups.any? %>
        <tr class="rails-table-preferences-demo-table__group-row">
          <% @demo_visible_column_groups.each do |group| %>
            <th colspan="<%= group["colspan"] %>"><%= group["label"] %></th>
          <% end %>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
      <tr>
        <% @demo_visible_columns.each do |column| %>
          <th data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="<%= column["key"] %>"><%= column["label"] %></th>
        <% end %>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% @orders.each do |order| %>
        <tr>
          <% @demo_visible_columns.each do |column| %>
            <% key = column["key"] %>
            <td data-rails-table-preferences-column-key="<%= key %>">
              <% case key %>
              <% when "delivery_date" %>
                <%= l(order[:delivery_date]) %>
              <% when "amount" %>
                <%= number_with_delimiter(order[:amount]) %>
              <% else %>
                <%= order[key.to_sym] %>
              <% end %>
            </td>
          <% end %>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  <% end %>
</div>
